pandas operations :
1. to_frame() : converts series to dataframe.
2. type(structure_name) : gives the type of data structure.
3. os.getcwd() : To get the current working path.
4. read_csv(file_name.csv) : To load the data from the csv file.
5. read_excel(file_name.xlsx) : To load the data from excel file.
6. read_json(file_name.json) : To load the data from json file.
7. read_sql(file_name.sql) : To load the data from sql file.
8. to_csv() or to_excel(),to_sql(),to_json() : storing data from dataframe to csv or excel or json or sql file.
9. shape : To know the shape of dataframe.
10. head() : gives top 5 rows or we can mention how many rows we want.
11. tail() : Gives bottom 5 rows or we can mention the number of rows from bottom we want.
12. sample() : Gives random samples of data.
13. rename : Rename the column name.
14. copy() : copies the original and creates the duplicate one.
15. rank(column_name) : Gives rank based on given column.
16. sort_values(column_name) : sorts values based on given column.
17. drop(column_name,axis = 1) : It drops a column
18. drop(columns = [col1,col2,col3]) : To drop multiple columns at a time.
19. column_name.unique() : finding unique values from the table of selected column.
20. replace(old_value,new_value) : replaces old_value to new_value.
21. dtypes : To know the data types of all the columns.
22. astype() : converts from one data type to another data type.
23. info() : gives about the entire tables information
24. select_dtypes(include = [col1,col2]) : selecting columns based on data types.
25. describe() : it describes the statistical information about the data.
26. table_name[condition] : Filtering based on conditions.
27. where(condition) : It returns the records which are satisfying a condition.
28. where(condition,constant_value) : it replaces nan value wit constant_value.
29. loc[rows_index,column_names] : It is used for slicing/Indexing
30. iloc[rows_index,columns_index] : here we mention only index numbers not the names.
31. at and iat are special version of loc and iloc and at and iat are faster than loc and iloc for single value update.
32. sort_values(column_name) : it sorts values based on the given column name.
33. set_index(column_name) : By default the index starts with 0 but by using this we can change.
34. reset_index(inplace = True) : it resets back into the original index and inplace will perform on the same data.
35. isnull() : can check if null values exist or not.
36. dropna() : It delete the records having null values.
37. dropna(axis=1) : it drops entire column having null values.
38. fillna(value) : fills null value with any constant value like mean or max like that.
39. duplicated() : returns true or false if there is duplicate values.
40. drop_duplicates() : It removes duplicate values.
41. title() : returns the fist index of string into capitalized.
42. lower() : converts string into lower case letters.
43. upper() : converts string into upper case letters.
44. strip() : removes extra spaces from left or right of strings.
45. apply() : lets you run the custom function on your dataset. like lambda function.
46. map() : mainly used for mapping of value.
47. sum() : sum of column values
48. min() : min value, idxmin() : id of min value.
49. max() : max value from column,idxmax() : id of max.
50. mean() : mean value or average value of column.
51. std() : standard deviation
52. var() : variance
53. median(),mode() : calculates mean or mode values.
54. groupby(column_name) : group the data based on subgroups.
55. merge(column_names,on = column_name,how = 'inner') : help to merge the df, based on common columns.
56. inner() : gives common values from both tables.
57. outer() : gives all data from both but common returns once only
58. left() : all records from left and common columns from right
59. right() : all from right and common from left.
60. join(column_name,how = '') : joins the df based on index.
61. concat() : combine df vertially or horizontally.
62. date_range(start,end) : it gives the date with difference of time based on start and end.
